<LENGTH>
<P>
76 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAHARA CLUB AND DESERT ENVIRONMENTALISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sahara Club, a group of plant-crushing motorcycle enthusiasts is aptly 
named. 
</P>
<P>
Large portions of the Sahara desert and other eroded wastelands of North Africa 
are man-made. In historical (that is, Roman Empire) times, many now ugly and 
hostile areas of North Africa were verdant and friendly. They became deserts 
after men cut down all of the trees and their goats nibbled all of the smaller 
plants out of existence. 
</P>
<P>
MARK SEECOF 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
