A recent case (of selective journalism) is the lack of coverage of the Screen 
Actors Guild's presentation of the "Annual Career Achievement Award" on Dec. 9 
to the prominent black actor Brock Peters. The 70,000 members of SAG honored 
Peters for his acting and humanitarian achievements during his lengthy career. 
