<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITAN WRESTLERS EDGE OKLAHOMA ON FINAL MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Jones scored a major decision victory in the heavyweight division to give 
Cal State Fullerton a 20-19 nonconference wrestling victory over Oklahoma 
Friday night at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (3-3) had a 16-13 lead going into the 190-pound match, in which 
Fullerton's Derrick Brown was disqualified when he bit Andy Foster to get out 
of a painful hold. 
</P>
<P>
The disqualification gave Oklahoma (1-2) a 19-16 lead, but Jones' 12-2 victory 
over Joe O'Mara was worth four points and the victory. 
</P>
<P>
In the first five individual matches, Titans Michael Grubbs, Jeff Maes, Lyndon 
Campbell and Marty Kouyoumtjian all won by decision, and Donnie Kiernan 
wrestled to a 7-7 draw with William Gay in the 142 class. But Oklahoma won 
three and had a draw in the next four weight classes to set up the deciding 
heavyweight match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
