<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRANDPA AND NEW KIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am Frank Sinatra's granddaughter and I'm writing about the article (Morning 
Report, Nov. 28) about my grandfather and the New Kids on the Block. First of 
all, I am 15 years old, not 12, and there must have been some misunderstanding 
about me and the New Kids. 
</P>
<P>
I told my grandpa that I thought it was a good idea if he made a recording with 
them, but I am not a "rabid New Kids fan" and it was not what I "wanted for 
Christmas." The credit should go to my grandfather because he asked me, or told 
me, about the idea months ago. I had nothing to do with it. He must have 
thought that I was a fan, but I really am not. The whole thing wasn't even my 
idea, so I shouldn't get any credit. 
</P>
<P>
I would appreciate it if this could be cleared up . . . and if you want to know 
who my favorite singer is, it's my grandpa! 
</P>
<P>
AMANDA LAMBERT 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
