<P>
THE TEST OF TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re David J. Fox's article on the mixed reaction to "Godfather III" at its first 
industry screening (Dec. 14): 
</P>
<P>
I for one can't wait to see the film. 
</P>
<P>
I'm sure not everyone remembers this, but the reactions to three of the 
greatest films of the 1960s -- "Bonnie and Clyde," "2001" and "The Wild Bunch" 
-- were decidedly mixed. People either hated them or loved them; there was no 
middle ground. But with the passage of time all three are now considered 
classics. 
</P>
<P>
STEVE BARR 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
