<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OJAI; 
</P>
<P>
HOT LINE TO HELP PROBLEM DRINKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A free 24-hour hot line for people experiencing alcohol or drug problems during 
the holiday season will be available through the New Beginnings treatment 
program at Ojai Valley Community Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
"We recognize chemical dependency as a family disease which affects the 
individual as well as loved ones and is especially difficult during the holiday 
season when feelings are more intense," said Mary Lythgoe, New Beginnings 
program director. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone experiencing a drug- or alcohol-related crisis can call New Beginnings 
at 805-646-5567 and talk with the professionally trained staff. The free 
service is completely confidential, Lythgoe said. GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
