<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEXICAN COMMUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the nicest developments for the fre-trade future agreements between 
Mexicoand the U.S. is the strong interest that the Mexican government is now 
showing in the 15-million-strong Mexican-American community, particularly for 
investment and expertise. 
</P>
<P>
Already it has established a "Program for Mexican Community Abroad" that is run 
from a special office in the Interior Ministry in Mexico City. 
</P>
<P>
A high government official has admitted that they have finally become aware of 
the growing political and economic importanceof the Mexican-American community. 
They want this community to "lobby for us in U.S. society much like the smaller 
U.S. Jewish population has championed successfully Israel's cause." 
</P>
<P>
Certainly our great state would benefit from all this since we have about half 
of all Mexican-Americans in America. Even a modest $10,000 investment in Mexico 
can bring hefty profits. With increasing success south of the border, the 
Mexicans will have more moneyto buy from us, particularly from our state. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN F. MENDEZ 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
