Reputed mob boss John Gotti must spend Christmas in jail because a federal 
judge refused to release him on bail pending a trial on racketeering and murder 
charges set for next year. District Judge I. Leo Glasser said the government 
had proved in a "clear and convincing" manner that there were no conditions of 
release that could "reasonably assure the safety of any other person in the 
community." After the three-hour hearing in the Brooklyn federal court, Glasser 
set Jan. 18 for the next hearing in the case. 
