<P>
CHILD MOLESTER HELD ON PAROLE CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police have arrested a convicted child molester on suspicion of violating his 
probation by being unsupervised in the company of a 14-year-old girl. 
</P>
<P>
John Pizzini, 30, of Costa Mesa was arrested Thursday at an undisclosed Costa 
Mesa residence, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Pizzini, who pleaded guilty to four counts of molesting a 14-year-old girl 
earlier this year, was released from jail in October after serving a 
three-month sentence. 
</P>
<P>
He was placed on three years' probation, which required him to register with 
police as a sex offender and stay away from minors. 
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Orange County district attorney's office asked for an 
investigation into whether Pizzini violated his probation by hiring minors to 
sell candy bars. 
</P>
