<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pru-Bache Says It Expects Big Loss: Prudential-Bache Securities Inc. will lose 
$250 million this year as it gets out of several costly businesses, according 
to its parent company. 
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the loss was bigger than expected. Perrin Long, a brokerage 
analyst at Lipper Analytical Securities, noted that part of the loss was 
because of a restructuring charge, which Prudential did not specify. He said 
the brokerage had lost $250 million in two problem areas: merchant banking and 
risk arbitrage. Any other profits were wiped out by the restructuring charge, 
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
